Volley Live Schema
Volley Live Schema : VolleyLive Element
VolleyLive Element
Description
Main element.

Data for the live information about a volleyball match.

The order of the elements is free.

Depending on the options specified by the caller, the received file can change.

You can download the schema file here.

Namespace (none)
Diagram
Overview
VolleyLive
Main element.

Data for the live information about a volleyball match.

The order of the elements is free.

Depending on the options specified by the caller, the received file can change.

You can download the schema file here.

IsBallInPlay optional xs:boolean
Indicates that the ball is currently in play. If the attribute is missing, the ball is not in play.
IsMatchPointTeamA optional xs:boolean
Indicates that team A will win the match if it wins the current rally. If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a match point. Otherwise, the IsSetPointTeamA attribute gives the ordinal number of match points for the set.
IsMatchPointTeamB optional xs:boolean
Indicates that team B will win the match if it wins the current rally. If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a match point. Otherwise, the IsSetPointTeamB attribute gives the ordinal number of match points for the set.
IsSetPointTeamA optional xs:nonNegativeInteger
Indicates that team A will win the set if it wins the current rally. If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a set point. The value of the attribute is the ordinal number of set points for the current set.
IsSetPointTeamB optional xs:nonNegativeInteger
Indicates that team B will win the set if it wins the current rally. If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a set point. The value of the attribute is the ordinal number of set points for the current set.
NoServingTeam optional xs:positiveInteger
Number of the team that is serving. When between rallies or between sets, this is the number of the team that will serve at the next rally or set. If the attribute is missing, this information is not available (match not started, finished, ...).
NoTeamAtLeft optional xs:positiveInteger
Number of the team at the left of the scorer table. When between rallies or between sets, this is the number of the team that will be at the left for the next rally or set. If the attribute is missing, this information is not available (match not started, finished, ...).
NoTeamAtRight optional xs:positiveInteger
Number of the team at the right of the scorer table. When between rallies or between sets, this is the number of the team that will be at the right for the next rally or set. If the attribute is missing, this information is not available (match not started, finished, ...).
PollDelay optional xs:double
Delay before the next poll, in seconds. The delay should start whe the answer is received from the web service. If The attribute is missing, the default delay is 20s.
Version required xs:positiveInteger
Version of the data. When requesting for an update, the client sends the version of the data it currently has and the web service doesn't need to send all the data again if it has not changed.
Choice 0..∞
LineUp VolleyLiveLineUp Complex Type
Current line-up. The players are listed starting at the first server and continuing in a counterclockwise direction. The element is missing if the line-up is unknown or the match is finished.
NoPlayer1 required xs:positiveInteger
Number of player 1. This is the player at the service position (back right).
NoPlayer2 required xs:positiveInteger
Number of player 2. This is the player in the front right.
NoPlayer3 required xs:positiveInteger
Number of player 3. This is the player in the front center.
NoPlayer4 required xs:positiveInteger
Number of player 4. This is the player in the front left.
NoPlayer5 required xs:positiveInteger
Number of player 5. This is the player in the back left.
NoPlayer6 required xs:positiveInteger
Number of player 6. This is the player in the back center.
NoTeam required xs:positiveInteger
Number of the team.

TimePlayed optional xs:nonNegativeInteger
The time played, in ms. The value is the sum of the durations of all the rallies. The attribute is optional: it is omitted if the time played can't be known. For this value to be calculated, the start time offset and end time offset of all the rallies must be known.

Attributes
NameTypeUseDefaultFixedDescription
IsBallInPlayxs:booleanoptional  Indicates that the ball is currently in play. If the attribute is missing, the ball is not in play.
IsMatchPointTeamAxs:booleanoptional  Indicates that team A will win the match if it wins the current rally. If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a match point. Otherwise, the IsSetPointTeamA attribute gives the ordinal number of match points for the set.
IsMatchPointTeamBxs:booleanoptional  Indicates that team B will win the match if it wins the current rally. If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a match point. Otherwise, the IsSetPointTeamB attribute gives the ordinal number of match points for the set.
IsSetPointTeamAxs:nonNegativeIntegeroptional  Indicates that team A will win the set if it wins the current rally. If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a set point. The value of the attribute is the ordinal number of set points for the current set.
IsSetPointTeamBxs:nonNegativeIntegeroptional  Indicates that team B will win the set if it wins the current rally. If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a set point. The value of the attribute is the ordinal number of set points for the current set.
NoServingTeamxs:positiveIntegeroptional  Number of the team that is serving. When between rallies or between sets, this is the number of the team that will serve at the next rally or set. If the attribute is missing, this information is not available (match not started, finished, ...).
NoTeamAtLeftxs:positiveIntegeroptional  Number of the team at the left of the scorer table. When between rallies or between sets, this is the number of the team that will be at the left for the next rally or set. If the attribute is missing, this information is not available (match not started, finished, ...).
NoTeamAtRightxs:positiveIntegeroptional  Number of the team at the right of the scorer table. When between rallies or between sets, this is the number of the team that will be at the right for the next rally or set. If the attribute is missing, this information is not available (match not started, finished, ...).
PollDelayxs:doubleoptional  Delay before the next poll, in seconds. The delay should start whe the answer is received from the web service. If The attribute is missing, the default delay is 20s.
Versionxs:positiveIntegerrequired  Version of the data. When requesting for an update, the client sends the version of the data it currently has and the web service doesn't need to send all the data again if it has not changed.

    <xs:attribute name="IsBallInPlay" type="xs:boolean">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Indicates that the ball is currently in play.
If the attribute is missing, the ball is not in play.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
    <xs:attribute name="IsMatchPointTeamA" type="xs:boolean">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Indicates that team A will win the match if it wins the current rally.
If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a match point.
Otherwise, the IsSetPointTeamA attribute gives the ordinal number of match points for the set.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
    <xs:attribute name="IsMatchPointTeamB" type="xs:boolean">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Indicates that team B will win the match if it wins the current rally.
If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a match point.
Otherwise, the IsSetPointTeamB attribute gives the ordinal number of match points for the set.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
    <xs:attribute name="IsSetPointTeamA" type="xs:nonNegativeInteger">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Indicates that team A will win the set if it wins the current rally.
If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a set point.
The value of the attribute is the ordinal number of set points for the current set.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
    <xs:attribute name="IsSetPointTeamB" type="xs:nonNegativeInteger">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Indicates that team B will win the set if it wins the current rally.
If the attribute is missing, the rally is not for a set point.
The value of the attribute is the ordinal number of set points for the current set.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
    <xs:attribute name="NoServingTeam" type="xs:positiveInteger">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Number of the team that is serving.
When between rallies or between sets, this is the number of the team that will serve at the next rally or set. If the attribute is missing, this information is not available (match not started, finished, ...).</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
    <xs:attribute name="NoTeamAtLeft" type="xs:positiveInteger">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Number of the team at the left of the scorer table.
When between rallies or between sets, this is the number of the team that will be at the left for the next rally or set. If the attribute is missing, this information is not available (match not started, finished, ...).
</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
    <xs:attribute name="NoTeamAtRight" type="xs:positiveInteger">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Number of the team at the right of the scorer table.
When between rallies or between sets, this is the number of the team that will be at the right for the next rally or set. If the attribute is missing, this information is not available (match not started, finished, ...).
</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
    <xs:attribute name="PollDelay" type="xs:double">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Delay before the next poll, in seconds.
The delay should start whe the answer is received from the web service.
If The attribute is missing, the default delay is 20s.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
    <xs:attribute name="Version" type="xs:positiveInteger" use="required">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>Version of the data.
When requesting for an update, the client sends the version of the data it currently has and the web service doesn't need to send all the data again if it has not changed.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:attribute>
